            "creation_date": 1503032302,
            "body": "<p>Start by setting your min and max correctly:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int min=Integer.MAX_VALUE, max=Integer.MIN_VALUE;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>which will ensure that the <code>min<\/code> and <code>max<\/code> <em>will<\/em> get updated.<\/p>\n\n<p>Second, as  I wrote in the comments, bail out of the loop immediately after reading <code>x<\/code> if <code>x<\/code> is negative:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>x = myScanner.nextInt();\nif (x &lt; 0) {\n    break;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Third, start reading <code>myScanner.nextInt<\/code> only inside the while loop.<\/p>\n\n<p>And last, get rid of the assignment:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>number = number++;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>change to:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>number++;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>because the operation <code>number++<\/code> doesn't return a value.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Important<\/strong>: It would be a good idea to learn how to work with a good IDE (for example: IntelliJ/Eclipse/Netbeans) and also learn how to work with a debugger. <\/p>\n\n<p>Full code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    Scanner myScanner = new Scanner(System.in);\n    int number=0; //number is to store number of inputs\n    int i=1; //i is to store current iteration\n    int sum=0; //sum is to store sum of the input\n    int x=0; //x is to store the user input\n    int min=Integer.MAX_VALUE, max=Integer.MIN_VALUE; // fix 1\n\n    while (x &gt;= 0){\n        System.out.println(\"Please input the next positive integer\");\n        x = myScanner.nextInt();\n        if (x &lt; 0) {  // fix 2\n            break;\n        }\n        if(x&gt;=0) {\n            sum = sum + x;\n            number++;   // fix 3\n            if (x &gt;= max)\n                max = x;\n            if (x &lt;= min)\n                min =x;\n            i++;\n        }\n    }\n    int average = sum/number;\n    System.out.println(\"The average is \" + average);\n    System.out.println(\"The minimum value is \" + min);\n    System.out.print( \"and the maximum value is \" + max);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Running the code, I'm getting the following output:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Please input the next positive integer\n1\nPlease input the next positive integer\n2\nPlease input the next positive integer\n3\nPlease input the next positive integer\n4\nPlease input the next positive integer\n5\nPlease input the next positive integer\n-1\nThe average is 3\nThe minimum value is 1\nand the maximum value is 5\nProcess finished with exit code 0\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 45748833,
            "question_id": 45747261,
            "last_edit_date": 1503070254
        },
