            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1503037426,
            "creation_date": 1503037426,
            "body": "<p>There was some issues in your code. First scanned integer value ignore in the calculation. And always min value is zero because 'int min = 0'\nI did some changes on your code try this.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n\n  Scanner myScanner = new Scanner(System.in);\n\n  System.out.println(\"Please input first integer\");\n  int number = 0; //number is to store number of inputs\n  int sum = 0; //sum is to store sum of the input\n  int x; //x is to store the user input\n  int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE, max = 0;\n\n  x = myScanner.nextInt();\n\n  while (x &gt;= 0) {\n    sum = sum + x;\n    number++;\n    if (x &gt;= max) {\n      max = x;\n    }\n    if (x &lt;= min) {\n      min = x;\n    }\n    System.out.println(\"Please input the next positive integer \");\n    x = myScanner.nextInt();\n  }\n\n  int average = sum / number;\n\n  System.out.println(\"The average is \" + average);\n  System.out.println(\"The minimum value is \" + min);\n  System.out.print(\"and the maximum value is \" + max);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 45749818,
            "question_id": 45747261
        },
